
[1]reciprocation

   RECIPROCA'TION, n. [L. reciprocatio.]

   1. Interchange of acts; a mutual giving and returning; as the
   reciprocation of kindnesses.

   2. Alternation; as the reciprocation of the sea in the flow and ebb of
   tides.

   3. Regular return or alternation of two symptoms or diseases.
